IV.
Although Aristotle seems inclined to award to Anax­ agoras the credit of a discovery of the existence in Nature of an efficient principle, yet he states that, prior to the Anaxagorean philosophy, Hermotimus, a native of Clazomenæ, was in actual possession of.
an ætiological theory of this kind.
