Aristotle, accordingly, sets down what he conceives to constitute the legitimate subjects of doubt in con­ nexion with Ontology or Metaphysics.
And, first, the question may be asked, Is Ontology, as a science of causes, single or manifold ?—is it conversant about the principles of substance merely, or also about those from whence all demonstrative reasoning is derived ?
