In the Ideal theory, we cannot put our finger upon a single efficient or alterative principle, nor can its advocates show what service it is that they propose conferring upon the interests of science in general by this hypothesis about forms.
They certainly cannot establish their asser­ tion of these ideas constituting the substance of things;
