Still, however, his asser­ tion of the necessity of the existence of a certain supra- sensual substance may fall very far short of a demon­ stration of God's existence;
and the examination of this point, of how far Aristotle had advanced in the develop­ ment of his theological system, may form not an unsuitable conclusion to the foregoing interpretation of his Ontology.
