THE according to which "1 is denominated in many ways.
In one way, indeed, as the species and the substance of each thing ;
as, for instance, that in accordance with which a man is good, itself is good;
and, in another way, as that in which first a thing has been fitted by nature to rise into being, as colour in a superficies.
