Now, if there is something that is eternal and immovable, and that involves a separate subsist­ ence, it is evident that it is the province of the speculative,2 that is, of the ontological, science to investigate such.
It is not, certainly, the province of physical science, at any rate, (for physical science is conversant about certain movable natures,) nor of the mathematical, but of a science prior to both of these, that is, the science of meta­ physics.
